nts1.d: DJ & producer Shy One oversees the chatroom nonsense and brings that necessary get-up-and-go vibe every single hump day…
Vibrant eclecticism from Portuguese selector Mafalda, for two hours every month.
Parisian party instigator Louise Chen pulls from a timeless well of classic & modern house, disco, soul, pop, & more.

Winding back to the early 2010s, delving into the explosion of new "underground" rap artists, taking the genre into interesting new aesthetics, including acts like Lofty305, Chris Travis, Lil B, and others, including acts that are now mainstream stars, such as A$AP Rocky and Denzel Curry. If you remember this the first time round you are now eligible for unc status. We don't make the rules.
LA-based duo 2D0GS welcome us to their world ahead of their new EP ALL THE D0GS ARE BARKING releasing on dh2 on March 6th.
Trips through the breakbeat portal with Tim Reaper, one of modern jungle's most vital talents.

Record maker, player and mixer Martelo - not Martello - joins the musical dots with sonic heat from across the globe. Taking us to hip-hop, RnB, electronica and elsewhere, Martelo keeps it tight and keeps the heat: non-stop classics.
Hi octane monthly missives from Naina & Sherelle, the minds behind the hybrid Jungle, Techno & Footwork label Hooversound.

Nkisi a.k.a Melika Ngombe Kolongo heads up a monthly late slot to rattle through dozens of tracks at breakneck speed, her mixes punctuated by African club beats and tinged by the jagged edges of gabber.
From the host: _"DJ, curator, and club culture worker .. percussions, booty bounce, discourse .. Rhythmachines & sounds of/from the global South & Black Atlantic, along diasporic movements & technological co-evolutions.
Recorded in Dhaka, with support from Siam & Turjo.
@mreadmwo"_

nts2.d: The underground and experimental hero, composer, and guitar abstractionist Oren Ambarchi invites us to regular eclectic listening sessions, exploring the breadth of his extensive record collection.
Irish indie songwriter Nashpaints jumps on for a guest show ahead of the release of his new record "Everyone Good Is Called Molly", playing original material, music from friends and inspirations.
Rose-tinted hallucinogenic sounds from Astral Vibes' Acid Memories. Illicit dealings in psychedelia of all persuasions. Sit back and enjoy…

A unique dip into the musical history of Ukraine with archival label Shukai, journeying back to the ‘90s, playing music from documentaries, sci-fi films, obscure cartoons and late-night music programming, curated by Dmytro Nikolaienko, Dmytro Prutkin and Alec Tsapenko.
From the host: "A journey into late-1980s and mid-1990s Ukrainian pop music: tracing a path from private tape archives to era’s largest music television platform ’Territory A‘."

80's Rampwalk delivers an hour of cold wave, minimal synth, industrial, post-punk and music made in Berlin basements.
From the host: "Présence, a Belgian label run by members of Isolation Ward, released some 16 or 17 cassettes during its 3 year run most of which are ifficult to hear. This month's show is a Présence primer, a tribute to a wonderful and strange label which has somehow mostly escaped the reissue-industrial complex."

nts2.n: IKR. IMPRINT w/ Adum Brate: The Terminal

nts2.d:
A riff on Jon Hassell's Fourth World series. Where Hassell focused on creating ritual music of potential societies that didn't exist; Ian Kim Judd seeks to evoke the notion of potential utopian societies that could exist. In these times of global instability and uncertainty, Fifth World seeks to posit an alternative, with scenes from an optimistic future.
From the host: "Canadian producer Khotin brings a characteristically dreamlike selection to Fifth World, weaving through ambient drift and downtempo reverie. The mix includes two unreleased productions alongside some kindred spirits. An hour of patient, textured music for anytime."

Jen Monroe writes the album download blog Listen To This!, which focuses on Japanese and new age records: Listen to This
From the host: "Drippy, yearny, violin-heavy romantic classical for Valentine's Day. Lay it on thick!"

nts2.d: Rising California bedroom pop songwriter Operelly and indie folk artist Zachshots share a romantic Valentine’s Day vibe…

nts2.d: Bill Spencer shares weekend recordings from his living room studio in Detroit, Michigan, from where he brings a range of soulful jazz rock, and ambient sounds, spanning to electronica and psychedelic dub.

nts2.d: LA native Bianca Lexis showcases a monthly, genre-blending hour, exploring the different facets of pop, rock, synth and house music. all in panoramic view, for you.

nts2.d:
Exploring inner and outer worlds, cosmic and pastoral sounds, and the intersection between reality and dreams once a month with Jocelyn Romo's mix of international and private press folk, instrumental guitar, dream country, ambient, new age, kosmiche, psych and beyond
From the host: "a valentine’s day special of 80s dream pop, soft rock, and dreamy new wave by women, for all lovers of falling in love."
Soft-touch home listening selections live from LA every month with Luke Mele. Traversing ambient, jazz, guitar tones and more.

Slowed Down, sun kissed journeys through dub, synth, cosmic & balearic beats. Brought to you from LA each month.
From the host: "Happy lunar new year transformations"

subtle.d: Potent Funk records’ Matt Frost - Well known for his technical abilities and Sleazy bass music style, Frost covers all angles from UK alt Rap to the LA beat scene.

Get ready to embark on a captivating sonic journey of underground music with Charlie Kelly. Including new and timeless sounds from the depths of rap, drill, grime, and experimental genres from the vibrant streets of the UK and beyond. Charlie unearths the very best in music that pushes boundaries. Off the mic, Charlie is a Radio Producer and Social Media Executive with an eclectic music taste spanning across many different cultures, decades, and styles. Hailing from North London with a love for audio and pop culture, you can expect to hear tune after tune when you’re locked into Charlie Kelly on Subtle.
BirdE brings an hour of the freshest Drum and Bass covering everything from liquid to techy steppers - the deeper the better.

Originally from Cambridge, Counter Culture's selection deftly navigates across a myriad of influences and exclusives from himself & friends.
Expect some of the freshest rolling soul straight to your headspace.

subtle.d:
Hailing from Mumbai, now living in London, Chaitu is energised by the UK sound and scene.

With a love of all things weird, weighty and groovy; his mixes and productions bridge electro, techno, breaks, UKG and Jungle, with sprinklings of everything in between.

Chaitu champions provocative beats that break down the barriers of style, genre and expectation, all while keeping you moving.

In:flux Audio are a record label based in Leeds, UK founded by production duo Tik&Borrow. Since the label's inception in October 2013, they have dabbled in multiple dance music styles with the emphasis always being on the tracks being unique, and packed full of bass. Today the primary output for the label is from their Dubstep roster and this is focus of their show on Subtle - giving the artists and remixers chance to showcase their sounds with an hour guest mix, all hosted by label bossman Tik.

I’m a 19 year old DJ and producer from Newcastle upon Tyne, mainly playing and producing music around the 140bpm mark. I started out playing old 2-step and jungle records, before moving my focus to mainly dubstep and grime. Along with my friends Pirata and White Label, I run Newcastle’s only current 140 night, Well Irie.
